                <h4>W3C&nbsp;Groups</h4>
                <dl>
                    <dt><a href="http://www.w3.org/html/wg/">HTML Working Group</a></dt>
                    <dd>To provide input on digital content, licensing, and payment metadata expression in the HTML5 and XHTML5 specifications.</dd>

                    <dt><a href="http://www.w3.org/2008/webapps/">Web Applications Working Group</a></dt>
                    <dd>To ensure that the API work around PaySwarming stays in line with the general
                    Web Applications work.</dd>
                    
					<dt><a href="http://www.w3.org/2001/tag/">Technical Architecture Group (TAG)</a></dt>
					<dd>To ensure that the PaySwarm transaction environment is in line with general Web Architecture Principles</dd>
					
                    <dt><a href="http://www.w3.org/2001/sw/CG/">Semantic Web Coordination Group</a></dt>
                    <dd>To ensure that the development of PaySwarming metadata expression and the PaySwarm APIs are coordinated with other
                    activities around the Semantic Web</dd>

                    <dt><a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/PF/">Protocols and Formats Working Group</a></dt>
                    <dd>To ensure that PaySwarm APIs can serve the accessibility needs of Web users from all walks of life.</dd>                    
                </dl>
                
